{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs-send-stream): 20 structured seeds across every SendCommand\nand error path\n\nfuzz_btrfs_send_stream feeds bytes into ffs_btrfs::parse_send_stream.\nThe format is `magic(13) | version(4) | command*` where each command\nis `cmd_len(4) | cmd_type(2) | crc32c(4) | data(cmd_len)` and the\nparser stops at the first End command (cmd=21). Existing 5 ad-hoc\nseeds (byte, empty, end, mkdir, truncated_attr) covered only a few\nvariants and never the CRC-mismatch / bad-magic / cmd-len-overrun\nerror paths.\n\nAdds 20 seeds spanning the SendCommand enum (Subvol/Snapshot/Mkfile/\nMkdir/Mknod/Mkfifo/Mksock/Symlink/Rename/Link/Unlink/Rmdir/SetXattr/\nRemoveXattr/Write/Clone/Truncate/Chmod/Chown/Utimes/End/UpdateExtent)\nand every documented error branch:\n\n  Happy paths (each with a properly-computed CRC32C tail):\n  * header-only (no commands)\n  * just End \u2014 minimal valid stream\n  * Subvol\u2192End / Snapshot\u2192End\n  * Mk-family chain (Mkfile + Mkdir + Mknod + End)\n  * Write + Truncate + End\n  * SetXattr + RemoveXattr + End\n  * Chmod + Chown + Utimes + End \u2014 full attribute update sequence\n  * UpdateExtent + End\n  * Rename + Link + Unlink + Rmdir + End \u2014 rename/link family\n  * Mkfifo + Mksock + Symlink + End \u2014 special-file family\n  * Clone + End\n  * realistic chain Subvol \u2192 Mkdir \u2192 SetXattr \u2192 Write \u2192 End\n\n  Error paths:\n  * trailing bytes after End \u2014 `trailing bytes after end command`\n  * 9 bytes after the version \u2014 InsufficientData on command header\n  * cmd_len declares 200 bytes but only 10 follow \u2014 InsufficientData\n    on command data\n  * deliberately bogus CRC field \u2014 `send_stream_crc32c mismatch`\n  * \"NOT-BTRFS-MAGIC\" prefix \u2014 `send_stream_magic` mismatch\n  * cmd_type = 999 (out of SendCommand enum range \u2014 parser must\n    fall back to Unspec but still validate cmd_len + crc)\n  * two consecutive End commands \u2014 parser must stop at the first\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 3.2 M executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
